This paper deals with quantum cryptography, specifically quantum money and collision-free quantum money. It also discusses the security of various cryptographic primitives such as signatures, hash functions, and commitment schemes. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT), complexity theory (cs.CC), and cryptography (cs.CRYPTO). Additionally, the paper involves the construction of polynomial systems (cs.DS).
